dreisoft.tresos.lib2.api.util

Class AbstractExecutableExtension

  • java.lang.Object
    • dreisoft.tresos.lib2.api.util.AbstractExecutableExtension
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IExecutableExtension
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractContext, AbstractPushOperation, DefaultHandler

    public abstract class AbstractExecutableExtension
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.eclipse.core.runtime.IExecutableExtension
    This is a default implementation of the IExecutableExtension interface for Eclipse "executable extensions". This class provides methods to easily access the executable extension's parameters, if the parameters are defined as subtags.

    A sample executable extension would look like this: 

     <sometag>
    <myExecExt class="MyClass" plugin="myPlugIn">
       <parameter name="myName" value="myValue">
    </myExecExt>
 </sometag>
    If the class MyClass is derived from this class, the value of the parameter myName can be accessed by calling the method getParameterValue(String).
    Since:
    2008.b
